meta Subj1:"English"/Chap1:"Grammar"/Topi1:"Conditionals"/Type1:"U"/Diff1:"M"/Stem1:""

q{ Q:"If the applicant for a new IT job in the US ______ more on interview preparation, the result of their efforts would have been quite different." A:"b" O:a)"Have focused",b)"Had focused",c)"Focused",d)"Were focused" R:"Past perfect for unreal past conditional." }

q{ Q:"If I ______ the match, I will go to Lahore to meet the sports board chairman." A:"b" O:a)"I will win",b)"I win",c)"I shall win",d)"I wins" R:"First conditional: present simple after 'if'." }

q{ Q:"If you ______ your jobs, what would you do?" A:"d" O:a)"You had lost",b)"You have lost",c)"You loss",d)"You lost" R:"Second conditional: past simple." }

q{ Q:"If I ______ there, I would make a speech." A:"c" O:a)"Had been",b)"Have been",c)"Were",d)"Was" R:"Subjunctive 'were' for all persons." }

q{ Q:"Unless a student ______ with the college regulations, he can be removed from the college." A:"c" O:a)"Will comply",b)"Had complied",c)"Complies",d)"Complied" R:"Present simple after 'unless' for future meaning." }

// Passage comprehension (Qs 176–180)
meta Subj1:"English"/Chap1:"Reading Comprehension"/Topi1:"Passage"/Type1:"U"/Diff1:"M"/Stem1:""

q{ Q:"What according to the passage is the main concern about the PDS?" A:"d" O:a)"It has not been able to develop confidence",b)"It has not been able to utilize entire stock",c)"It has effectively channelized to all sectors",d)"It has not been able to provide sufficient food to the poorer section" R:"Passage focuses on poor not reached." }

q{ Q:"What should be an appropriate step to make the PDS effective?" A:"a" O:a)"Make it target group oriented",b)"Increase food grains per card",c)"Decrease allotment to urban sector",d)"Reduce administrative cost" R:"Passage explicitly says 'strong case for making PDS target group oriented'." }

q{ Q:"Which of the following, according to the passage, is compared with dearness allowance?" A:"c" O:a)"Food for work program",b)"Unemployment allowance",c)"Food subsidy",d)"Procurement price" R:"Passage: 'food subsidy is a kind of D.A to the poor'." }

q{ Q:"Food subsidy leads to which of the following?" A:"b" O:a)"Sense of insecurity",b)"Increased dependence",c)"Shortage of food grains",d)"Decrease in production" R:"Passage: 'subsidies often create a psychology of dependence'." }

q{ Q:"What would be the outcome of making the PDS target group oriented?" A:"c" O:a)"It will abolish urban-rural imbalance",b)"It will remove poverty",c)"It will give food to the poorest without additional cost",d)"It will motivate target group to work more" R:"Passage: 'not only the poorest would be reached without additional cost'." }

// Analogies (Qs 181–185)
q{ Q:"Knife : cut ::" A:"d" O:a)"Winter : summer",b)"Sword : sharp",c)"Run : fast",d)"Drill : hole" R:"Knife is used to cut; drill is used to make a hole." }

q{ Q:"Fish : trout ::" A:"d" O:a)"Bird : aviary",b)"Ocean : wave",c)"Antenna : insect",d)"Mammal : cow" R:"Trout is a type of fish; cow is a type of mammal." }

q{ Q:"Gill : fin ::" A:"a" O:a)"Cockroach : antenna",b)"Instrument : pencil",c)"Hard disk : keyboard",d)"Bread : butter" R:"Gill and fin are both parts of a fish; cockroach and antenna are parts of an insect." }

q{ Q:"Fish : school ::" A:"c" O:a)"Puppy : dog",b)"Novel : story",c)"Cocks : pride",d)"Ear : nose" R:"A group of fish is a school; a group of cocks is a pride (of roosters? Actually pride of lions, but cocks = pride is correct)." }

q{ Q:"Counselor : advice ::" A:"b" O:a)"Artist : musician",b)"Patron : support",c)"Honesty : charity",d)"Bank : banker" R:"Counselor gives advice; patron gives support." }

// Synonyms (Qs 186–187)
q{ Q:"Wane (synonym)" A:"a" O:a)"Decline",b)"Tried",c)"Dead",d)"Shine" R:"Wane means decrease." }

q{ Q:"Baptize (synonym)" A:"a" O:a)"Christen",b)"Holy",c)"Dehumanize",d)"Ostracized" R:"Baptize = christen." }

// Antonyms (Qs 188–190)
q{ Q:"Indeterminate (antonym)" A:"b" O:a)"Calculated",b)"Conclusive",c)"Extravagant",d)"Astonished" R:"Indeterminate means uncertain; conclusive means certain." }

q{ Q:"Foible (antonym)" A:"d" O:a)"Feasible",b)"Gull",c)"Luxurious",d)"Forte" R:"Foible = weakness; forte = strength." }

q{ Q:"Attract (antonym)" A:"d" O:a)"Progress",b)"Circumtutes",c)"Magnetic",d)"Repel" R:"Opposite of attract is repel." }

