meta Subj1:"General Knowledge"/Chap1:"Current Affairs"/Topi1:"2014"/Type1:"K"/Diff1:"M"/Stem1:""

q{ Q:"Who is current chairman of ICC?" A:"c" O:a)"Percy Sonn",b)"David Morgan",c)"Srinivasan",d)"Sharad Pawar" R:"N. Srinivasan was ICC chairman in 2014." }

q{ Q:"Name of the country whose court sentenced 30 people to death over heroin smuggling in the largest such trial ever held." A:"d" O:a)"Brazil",b)"Korea",c)"France",d)"Vietnam" R:"Vietnam had such a trial." }

q{ Q:"Who is appointed as president of National Bank of Pakistan by the government?" A:"a" O:a)"Syed Ahmad Iqbal Ashraf",b)"Waqar Qureshi",c)"Jamal Din",d)"Akhtar Hussain" R:"Syed Ahmad Iqbal Ashraf was appointed in 2014." }

q{ Q:"Which country declared a state of emergency in its capital and surrounding areas to take protests aimed at overthrowing the government?" A:"d" O:a)"Austria",b)"China",c)"Croatia",d)"Thailand" R:"Thailand declared emergency in 2014." }

q{ Q:"When did Pakistan and Saudi Arabia sign the Hajj agreement at the Hajj ministry of Saudi Arabia?" A:"b" O:a)"16/1/2014",b)"22/1/2014",c)"18/1/2014",d)"26/1/2014" R:"22 January 2014." }

q{ Q:"Who was awarded the Ulysses Award 2013 for lifetime achievement by UNWTO for promoting sustainable tourism?" A:"a" O:a)"Dr. Tajveer Singh",b)"Richard Quest",c)"Dr. Gurbakhsh",d)"Aleni Shiror" R:"Dr. Taleb Rifai? Not sure. Option a as guess." }

q{ Q:"Which country allowed Sikhs to wear a turban while serving in the military?" A:"a" O:a)"UK",b)"USA",c)"France",d)"Germany" R:"UK allows turban in military." }

q{ Q:"'Duty: Memoirs of a Secretary at War' is written by" A:"a" O:a)"Robert Gates",b)"Michael Johnson",c)"Hector Fanky",d)"Timber McCollum" R:"Robert Gates wrote it." }

q{ Q:"Who won the Australian Open Men's singles title on 26th January 2014?" A:"d" O:a)"Rafael Nadal",b)"Roger Federer",c)"Andy Murray",d)"Stanislas Wawrinka" R:"Wawrinka defeated Nadal." }

q{ Q:"Which country won the female gold in a match played in the Lusofonia Games 2014?" A:"c" O:a)"Angola",b)"Mozambique",c)"Brazil",d)"India" R:"Brazil won." }

